.TH "snd_soc_component_test_bits" 9 "snd_soc_component_test_bits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_soc_component_test_bits \- Test register for change
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_soc_component_test_bits
.BI "(struct snd_soc_component *component "  ","
.BI "unsigned int reg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned int value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "component" 12
component
.IP "reg" 12
Register to test
.IP "mask" 12
Mask that specifies which bits to test
.IP "value" 12
Value to test against
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Tests a register with a new value and checks if the new value is
different from the old value.
.SH "RETURN"
1 for change, otherwise 0.
